'''Wanishita Shrine'''（わにしたじんじゃ）is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in Yokota-chō, {{ill|lt=Yamatokōriyama|Q118213|WD=Q118213|1=Yamatokōriyama}}, {{ill|lt=Nara Prefecture|Q131287|WD=Q131287|1=Nara Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|lt=Shikinai Shosha|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|lt=Shikinai small shrine|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}; under the former {{ill|lt=shrine ranking|Q10444029|WD=Q10444029|1=Shakaku}} system it was a {{ill|lt=Sonsha|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}, and it was also a {{ill|lt=beihei-sha|Q712534|WD=Q712534|lt=shrine receiving offerings|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}}{{sfn|奈良県史|p=54}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* {{ill|lt=Susanoo|Q272993|WD=Q272993|lt=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|1=Susanoo-no-Mikoto}} - enshrined at the center{{sfn|奈良県史|p=329}}.
* {{ill|lt=Ōkuninushi|Q276944|WD=Q276944|lt=Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto|1=Ōkuninushi}} - enshrined on the left{{sfn|奈良県史|p=329}}.
* {{ill|WD=Q505469|lt=Kushinadahime|Q505469|WD=Q505469|WD=Q505469|lt=Kushinadahime-no-Mikoto|1=Kushinadahime}} - enshrined on the right{{sfn|奈良県史|p=329}}.

=== History ===
It is located on the south bank about 1.5 {{ill|lt=kilometer|Q828224|WD=Q828224|1=Kilometre}} from the confluence of the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Takase River (Nara)|1=UNKNOWN}} and {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Wani River|1=UNKNOWN}}, facing the old {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Tatsuta Road|1=UNKNOWN}}{{sfn|奈良県史|p=329}}{{sfn|寺院神社大事典|p=832}}. In contrast to {{ill|lt=Wanishita Shrine (Tenri)|Q59282589|WD=Q59282589|lt=Wanishita Shrine|1=Wanishita Shrine (Ichinomoto)}} in {{ill|lt=Tenri|Q502196|WD=Q502196|1=Tenri, Nara}}, about 2.5 km east, this shrine is also called Shimoharumichi-no-miya (or Shimojidō-gu) and Shimoharumichi Tennō{{sfn|寺院神社大事典|p=832}}. It is regarded as one of the two seats of '''Wajirimo Shrine''' listed in {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} under {{ill|lt=Soekami District|Q7553491|WD=Q7553491|1=Soekami District, Nara}}{{sfn|寺院神社大事典|p=832}}.

The area around the shrine is believed to have been the base of the Sakurai clan, a branch of the {{ill|lt=Wani clan|Q11417873|WD=Q11417873|1=Wani clan}}, and artifacts dating to the {{ill|lt=Yayoi period|Q207858|WD=Q207858|1=Yayoi period}} have been excavated from Yokota Shimoike north of the shrine. It is thought this shrine originally enshrined the ancestral deity of the Sakurai clan, and that its source deity may have been the Wani clan ancestor {{ill|lt=Ame no Tarashihiko Kunioshiwake no Mikoto|Q11443593|WD=Q11443593|1=Prince Ametarashihiko}}{{sfn|奈良県史|p=329}}. It is said the ujiko extended as far south as {{ill|lt=Yamashiro Province|Q749276|WD=Q749276|1=Yamashiro Province}}'s {{ill|lt=Hōsono Village|Q30937308|WD=Q30937308|1=Hōsono}}{{sfn|奈良県史|p=329}}.

=== Precincts ===
[[File:Wanishita Shrine (Yokota) Keidai.jpg|thumb|200px|Precincts]]
=== Honden ===
A two-bay {{ill|lt=nagare-zukuri|Q210684|WD=Q210684|1=Nagare-zukuri}} structure with copper-plate roofing{{sfn|奈良県史|p=304}}. Records state that the former shrine building of Mizutani Shrine, a subsidiary shrine of {{ill|lt=Kasuga Taisha|Q714559|WD=Q714559|1=Kasuga-taisha}}, was transferred here in Kan'ei 10 ({{ill|lt=1633|Q6870|WD=Q6870|1=1633}}){{sfn|奈良県史 建築|p=911}}.

=== Sub-shrines ===
; East of main sanctuary
* Kasuga Wakamiya Shrine{{sfn|奈良県史|p=304}}
* Konpira-gū{{sfn|奈良県史|p=304}}
* Amaterasu Kōtai Jingū{{sfn|奈良県史|p=304}}
* Kasuga Daimyōjin{{sfn|奈良県史|p=304}}

; West of main sanctuary<ref group="注釈">This list follows the Nara Prefectural History description, but as of August 2018 differs from the actual sub-shrines on site. Specifically, Suwa and Ebisu shrines are not present, and instead Itsukushima, Komori, and Kōra shrines are enshrined.</ref>
* Hachiman Shrine{{sfn|奈良県史|p=304}}
* Sumiyoshi Shrine{{sfn|奈良県史|p=304}}
* Hakusan Shrine{{sfn|奈良県史|p=304}}
